quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"Does he not know, that when all the contents of the graves are disgorged"
  100,10,And all the secrets buried in the hearts are divulged
  100,11,"That day, (they would learn that) their Lord is thoroughly Knowledgeable about their deeds"
  101,1,That awesome (stunning) disaster
  101,2,What is (that) awesome disaster
  101,3,What do you suppose is that awesome disaster
  101,4,"That day, people would be like scattered (confused) moths"
  101,5,And the mountains like the fluffy tufts of colored wool
  101,6,Anyone whose scales (of good deeds) weigh heavier
  101,7,Would live in a state of bliss
  101,8,As for the one whose scale (of good deeds) is lighter
  101,9,An abysmal pit would totally engulf him
  101,10,And what do you think is (the content of) the abysmal pit
  101,11,Hot blazing fire
  102,1,"(Oh men! Your obsession to attain, hoard and show off) opulence diverts you (and keeps you busy)"
  102,2,Right until you land in (your) graves
  102,3,"No, surely not! You shall soon find out"
  102,4,"Again, be sure! You shall soon find out"
  102,5,"No, of course not! If you only knew with certainty"
  102,6,You shall surely see hell
  102,7,"Then, you would really see it with the eye of certainty"
  102,8,"And then, you would certainly be called to account for the blessings and the bounties"
  103,1,(I swear) by Time
  103,2,"Indeed, mankind happens to be in a state of a grave loss"
  103,3,"Except for those who believe, perform good deeds, strive for the truth, and strive with patience and perseverance"
  104,1,Misery is for the slanderer and the backbiter
  104,2,The one who gathers wealth; and counts it (zestfully)
  104,3,And thinks that his wealth confers immortality
  104,4,Of course not! He will certainly be flung into the ´Wrecker´
  104,5,And what do you suppose is the ´Wrecker´
  104,6,"(It is) the fire of Allah, kindled ablaze"
  104,7,Which will rise (and reach) up to (clutch) the hearts
  104,8,"Indeed, an inverted dome (of fire) would be (placed) upon them"
  104,9,Enclosed in (a fence of) tall pillars
  105,1,Are you not aware of how your Lord dealt with the army accompanied by the elephants
  105,2,Did He not make their (evil) plans go awry
  105,3,He let loose upon them a large flock of birds
  105,4,That pelted them with pellets made of baked clay
  105,5,"Thus, He turned them into the chewed out chaff"
  106,1,(The tribe of) Quraish is well known
  106,2,Renowned for their summer and winter journeys
  106,3,They should (devotedly) worship the Lord of this house (the ´Kaaba´ in Makkah)
  106,4,"Who feeds them, and protects them from (famine and) hunger. And secures them from (danger and) fear"
  107,1,Haven´t you seen the one who rejects the fact of the reward and punishment
  107,2,He is (really) the one who (shoos and) shoves away the orphans harshly
  107,3,And does not promote the feeding of the poor
  107,4,"Of course, misery is for (some of) those who perform ´salat´"
  107,5,"Those among them who stay unmindful of their \"salat´"
  107,6,Those who aim to be seen (doing good)
  107,7,And they hold back even minor favors
  108,1,"For sure, We granted you (excellence and) abundance"
  108,2,"So pray only to your Lord, and offer sacrifice"
  108,3,"For anyone who hates you, will be cut off (from your Lord´s mercy)"
  109,1,"Say, \"Oh you unbelievers"
  109,2,That which you worship is not what I worship
  109,3,And you are not going to worship the One that I worship
  109,4,I shall never worship that which you serve so devotedly
  109,5,Nor will you worship Whom I worship
  109,6,"You have your faith, and I have mine"
  110,1,"Once Allah´s help _ and with it, the victory _ arrives"
  110,2,You shall see people throng (and embrace) the religion of Allah in large numbers
  110,3,"So chant the praises of your Lord, and beg His forgiveness. Of course, it is really He Who accepts repentance and grants forgiveness"
  111,1,May the hands of Abu Lahab _ (an uncle of the Prophet) _ perish; and so may he
  111,2,"(All) his wealth, and everything he has earned failed him"
  111,3,"Soon, he will roast in the blazing fire"
  111,4,"And his woman, that tale-bearing malicious gossip"
  111,5,Shall have a rope of palm fibers around her neck
  112,1,"Say \"He _ (Allah) _ is One, (the most Unique)"
  112,2,"Allah is the Self-sufficient Master _ (the Ultimate Source, the Uncaused Cause)"
  112,3,"He did not beget, and He was not begotten"
  112,4,"And, there is absolutely no one equal to Him; no one is even remotely comparable"
  113,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge with (Allah), the Lord of the nascent dawn"
  113,2,From the evil He has created
  113,3,From the evil of darkness as it deepens (during the night)
  113,4,"From the evil of (women practicing) witchcraft, and blowing (spells) over knotted ropes"
  113,5,"And from the evil of the grudgeful, as he turns green with jealousy"
  114,1,"Say, \"I seek refuge with the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,The King of mankind
  114,3,The God of mankind
  114,4,(I seek refuge) from the evil of the devil _ (the whispering tempter)
  114,5,The one who (breathes doubts and) whispers in the hearts of mankind
  114,6,Amongst the jinn and the human kind